Data Validation Rules for OnlineBankingSystem
Input / Operation	Validation Rule	Description / Error Message
Account Name	Non-empty	Name cannot be empty.
Password	Minimum 4 chars	Password too short.
Initial Deposit	>= 0	Amount must be non-negative.
Account ID (login, transfer)	Integer, existing in accountMap	Input must be a valid number; Account must exist.
Deposit Amount	> 0	Deposit must be positive.
Withdraw Amount	> 0 and <= balance (or overdraft limit for CurrentAccount)	Withdraw amount must be positive and not exceed allowed balance; error messages:

"Amount must be > 0"

"Insufficient funds"

"Overdraft Limit exceeded" |
| Multithread Transaction Amount | Same as deposit/withdraw rules | Threads respect synchronized account balance updates. |
| Menu Choice (Main / Account Menu) | Valid integer in allowed range | Invalid choice shows: "Invalid option." |
| Close Account (if implemented) | Balance must be 0 | Cannot close account with remaining funds. |
| Account Map / DB Synchronization | Must exist in-memory and in DB | AccountMap must be updated with new accounts; DB must match. |

Examples from Your Code

1.Name Validation

String name = sc.nextLine().trim();
if (name.isEmpty()) {
    System.out.println("Name cannot be empty.");
    return;
}


2.Password Validation

String pass = sc.nextLine();
if (pass.length() < 4) {
    System.out.println("Password too short.");
    return;
}


3.Deposit/Withdraw Validation

if (amt <= 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("Deposit must be > 0");
if (amt > balance) throw new Exception("Insufficient funds");


4.Account ID Validation

IAccount acc = accountMap.get(id);
if (acc == null) {
    System.out.println("Not found!");
    return;
}
